Mimix Journal Replication — Active/Passive Asynchronous
IBM i production workloads run on the primary CoLo (PRODDSS) partition while the Temple (PRODDSS/Temple) site remains passive. Mimix continuously replicates data between sites using IBM journal-based replication across all configured datagroups. Replication is asynchronous — transactions are committed on the primary before being shipped to the DR site. If the primary CoLo site fails, Mimix datagroups are ended and cleared, the floating IP (10.7.1.169) is moved via ENDTCPIFC/STRTCPIFC, RDB directory entries (ADDRDDBDIRE) are updated, and Mimix is restarted on Temple. The Turnover IFS key must be manually applied at each DR event as it does not replicate automatically.

DASD Replication — Active/Passive Asynchronous
z/OS workloads (JES2, CICS, DB2, MQ) run exclusively on the primary Temple Data Center LPARs (JESB, JESA, JESC) while the CoLo facility remains passive. Dell PowerMax (3328/3329) storage arrays replicate data asynchronously to CoLo via SRDF/RDF — writes are acknowledged on the primary before being mirrored to DR volumes. If the primary site fails, CoLo LPARs are IPL'd, DB2 recovery jobs (DRGRECT/DRGRECP) are executed, MQ queue managers (MQPA/MQTA) are brought online, CICS regions are started sequentially, and BMC Control-M batch workloads are redirected to CoLo resources.

Mimix Journal Replication — Active/Passive Asynchronous
IBM i production workloads run on the primary CoLo (PRODDSS) while Temple remains passive. Mimix replicates data asynchronously via journal-based datagroups. On failover, datagroups are ended, the floating IP (10.7.1.169) is switched, RDB directory entries updated, and Mimix restarted on Temple with the Turnover IFS key manually applied.

DASD Replication — Active/Passive Asynchronous
z/OS workloads (JES2, CICS, DB2, MQ) run on the primary Temple Data Center (JESB/JESA/JESC) while CoLo remains passive. Dell PowerMax replicates storage asynchronously to CoLo via SRDF/RDF. On failover, CoLo LPARs are IPL'd, DB2 recovery jobs executed, MQ queue managers and CICS regions started, and Control-M batch workloads redirected to CoLo.
